It’s not all that often that you get a refreshed model, where at first glance the updated car looks quite a lot different to the model it replaces. Normally it’s a subtle exterior nip and tuck and a bit of an upgrade to the interior, but this is not the case with the facelift Mitsubishi ASX. The biggest change is that the updated ASX now features Mitsubishi’s new brand identity up front and that means there is a new bonnet, LED headlights and LED daytime running lights (DRL) as well as LED fog lamps with integrated turning signals, wrapped up with...